Durban - The funeral of a Chatsworth teenager was fatally shot during an alleged family dispute at his home on Sunday evening will take place today. Dilano Govender, 19, of Bayview, sustained gunshots wound to the neck and the leg. He died while en-route RK Khan Hospital. Police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane said on Monday a 32-year-old suspected handed himself over to police. "The suspect was charged with murder and is expected to appear in the Chatsworth Magistrate's Court on Tuesday.Â  His licensed firearm was also handed to the police and will be taken for ballistic testing," said Zwane. The victim's aunt, Devarani Govender, said his parents, Cheryl and Eugene, and younger brother, Donnel, were unable to accept his death. "We cannot believe he was taken from us in such a cruel manner. We are justice and those responsible to be brought to book." The funeral will take place at the Mobeni Height's Cemetery. Daily News